cpwd

A lightweight CLI password management tool.

Overview
cpwd (Command-line Password Manager) is a simple yet effective CLI tool for managing your passwords from the terminal.

Features
- Simple and intuitive command-line interface
- Minimal dependencies
- Easy to install and use

Usage
Basic commands to get started:
cpwd --help     # Display help and available commands
cpwd --version  # Show version information

Building from Source
1. Install dependencies on Debin/Ubuntu
   sudo apt update
   sudo apt install gcc autotools-dev autoconf # for build system
   sudo apt install help2man texinfo # for man and doc

   Install dependencies on Fedora
   sudo dnf install gcc autoconf automake # for build system
   sudo dnf install help2man texinfo # for man and doc

2A. Clone the repository:
    git clone https://github.com/nullzeiger/cpwd.git
    cd cpwd

3A. Build using make:
    sh ./bootstrap
    ./configure # for more info use ./configure --help
    make

2B. Build from .tar.gz:
    Download latest version https://github.com/nullzeiger/cpwd/releases
    tar -xf cpwd-1.6.1.tar.gz
    cd cpwd-1.6.1

3B. Build using make:
    ./configure # for more info use ./configure --help
    make

4. Test
	make check

5. Install (optional):
	sudo make install

